documentation.text: A classifier that can take a data sample as input and return a predict classification/label for the data.

Initialize a classifier.
@param _classifications The possible classifications that can be predicted.
@return The number of possible classifications that can be predicted.
@return The number of feature indices to use. 0 means to use all feature from the encoding.

@param data A single sample.
@return The normalization scalar for `data`.

@param data A single sample.
@return The predicted classification/label for `data`.

@param _classifications The possible classifications that can be predicted.

@param data A single sample.

params._featureIndices: The feature indices to append to the array held by this contract.

returns._0: The number of possible classifications that can be predicted.
The number of feature indices to use. 0 means to use all feature from the encoding.

addFeatureIndices(uint32[]).notice: Add more feature indices to take from the encoded result. Made to be called just after the contract is created and never again.
